Title

Review Existing Content Migration Workflow on Preview Server

Description

Review the content migration process currently used on the Preview server to understand how content is imported, what steps and tools are involved, and identify any gaps or improvements needed in the workflow.

Acceptance Criteria

Given the content migration workflow exists on the Preview server,
When the workflow is reviewed end-to-end,
Then all steps, tools, content types, and gaps must be clearly documented for further optimization.

Usage Document for Recipe Module

Description

Create a usage document that explains how to use the Recipe Module, including steps for creating, editing, publishing, and managing recipe items, along with any configuration options and best practices for users.

Acceptance Criteria

Given the Recipe Module functionalities are available,
When the usage document is created,
Then it should clearly cover creation, editing, publishing, configuration steps, and best-practice guidance for using the module.


Feedback Form – Tech Writers and Use Cases Documentation

Description

Prepare documentation for tech writers outlining how the feedback form works, including its purpose, workflow, available fields, expected behaviors, and different use cases where the form should be utilized. The document should help writers understand when and how to reference or incorporate the feedback form in content.

Acceptance Criteria

Given the feedback form functionality is available,
When the documentation for tech writers is created,
Then it should clearly describe the form’s purpose, workflow, field usage, and all relevant use cases for proper content integration.


Update Deployment Script to Retain Client Email List

Description

Update the deployment script so that the client email list (client email taxonomy/data) is retained during deployments and environment refreshes, ensuring it is not wiped, overwritten, or reset as part of the deployment process.

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN the deployment script is updated,
WHEN a deployment or environment refresh is executed,
THEN the client email list must remain intact and unchanged, with all existing entries preserved.

Title

Identify Technical Gaps and Dependencies for Preview IT Migration

Description

Analyze the Preview IT environment and identify all technical gaps, blockers, and dependencies that must be addressed before migrating or upgrading the environment. This includes reviewing infrastructure, configurations, integrations, modules, data dependencies, and deployment requirements.

Acceptance Criteria

Given the Preview IT environment is reviewed,
When the analysis is completed,
Then all technical gaps, dependencies, and required actions must be documented clearly for planning the migration.


Assessment for Preview IT Migration Compatibility

Description

Perform an assessment to evaluate the compatibility of the current Preview IT environment for the upcoming migration. This includes reviewing system configurations, module compatibility, infrastructure readiness, integrations, data flow, and any risks or blockers that may impact the migration process.

Acceptance Criteria

Given the Preview IT environment needs to be evaluated for migration,
When the compatibility assessment is completed,
Then all compatibility findings, risks, and required changes must be documented clearly for migration planning.

Title

Prepare High-Level IT Migration Deployment Plan

Description

Create a high-level deployment plan outlining the steps, prerequisites, sequencing, environments involved, risks, and key activities required for the IT environment migration. The plan should provide a clear overview of the migration flow and guide teams during execution.

Acceptance Criteria

Given the IT migration requirements are defined,
When the high-level deployment plan is prepared,
Then it should clearly document migration steps, dependencies, timelines, risks, and required actions for successful IT migration.

Create Detailed Pre-Migration Checklist for IT Environment

Description

Prepare a detailed pre-migration checklist for the IT environment covering all prerequisite activities, validations, configuration checks, backups, access requirements, and dependency confirmations needed before starting the migration. The checklist should ensure the environment is fully ready and no critical step is missed.

Acceptance Criteria

Given the IT environment is planned for migration,
When the detailed pre-migration checklist is created,
Then it should include all required validations, backups, configuration checks, access preparations, and dependency confirmations needed before migration begins.


